HEADWORD: Caliver
<hw>Cal"i*ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Corrupted fr.
<ets>caliber</ets>.]</ety> <def>An early form of hand gun, a variety of
the arquebus; originally a gun having a regular size of bore.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

